# React Performance & State Management

Favor memoization, colocation, and context over prop drilling; measure interactions and avoid unnecessary re-renders.

**Justification:** Keeps UI responsive, especially on low-end hardware and long call sessions.

## Memoization & Derived Data

Memoize expensive computations and callbacks where it matters.

```typescript
const visible = useMemo(() => items.filter(f), [items, f]);
```

## State Management

- Co-locate state with consumers when possible
- Use context for global app-level state like auth and feature flags

